                            <comment id="79506" author="webmeiker" created="Fri, 1 Jun 2012 02:12:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In the meantime, if someone wants to use authorize functions and &amp;lt;sec:authentication&amp;gt; tag of Spring Security 3.1.0 with JSF 2.0, this should help (see attachment)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="80863" author="grozniecki" created="Thu, 21 Jun 2012 06:30:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also, reference to WebSecurityExpressionHandler in Spring Manual (in &lt;a href=&quot;http://static.springsource.org/spring-security/site/docs/3.1.x/reference/springsecurity-single.html#d0e6860&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://static.springsource.org/spring-security/site/docs/3.1.x/reference/springsecurity-single.html#d0e6860&lt;/a&gt;) should be removed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="81242" author="rwinch" created="Thu, 28 Jun 2012 08:41:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Grzegorz,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank you for pointing this out. You are correct that should be removed. However, it isn&apos;t exactly the same as this issue so I went ahead and created a separate ticket for it (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-1985&quot; title=&quot; WebSecurityExpressionHandler in reference should be removed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SEC-1985&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SEC-1985&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). Thanks again for taking the time to help may Spring Security better.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="81245" author="rwinch" created="Thu, 28 Jun 2012 11:11:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have logged &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SWF-1557&quot; title=&quot;Consider consolidating SWF security tags&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SWF-1557&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SWF-1557&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to address consolidating SWF&apos;s Security taglib with Spring Security&apos;s taglib.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
